column5: If I am reading the regs correctly, Lake Dalrymple is open all year for Pike.  Does anyone know if this is the first year for an open season on pike fishing on Dalrymple?  Thanks  Sherriff
I think you can fish it all year around since last year, i was fishing Canal and Mitchel for pike this season already. I saw a lot of people fishing without any luck.
You are correct, pike are open all year in Zone 17. I believe it's been going on for a few years now.
The new rules started last year, hope to get out this weekend
